cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 125 mi SSW of Great Exuma Island
cyclone.trajectory: Moving WNW across eastern-central Cuba today, forecast to turn NW, pass near the Florida Keys Saturday, come ashore on the west coast / Big Bend of Florida late Sunday-Monday, then track inland across the Southeast U.S.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Big Bend / eastern Florida Panhandle

weather_observation.wind: None – gale-force probabilities remain near 0% for NY/NJ.
